cs.NE, cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

The paper focuses on the use of machine learning techniques, specifically neural networks, for modeling computer networks. This falls under the category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Networked and Distributed Computing (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper evaluates the accuracy of the models, which is a common topic in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper aims to provide practical guidelines, which is related to Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
